<p>I am using RedBeanPHP to update row in the database, but    IMPORT    method does not skip paramters with unset values and still updates those fields. There is some code snipets below:</p>  <pre><code>class Section {    public $hours;   public $title;   public $body;   public $live;   public $published;   public $highlighted;   public $highlight_colour;   public $created_at;   public $created_by;   public $modified_at;   public $modified_by;   public $deleted;    public function update($id)   {     $section = R::load('pref_sections', $id);     $section-&gt;import($this);     R::store($section);   } } </code></pre>  <p>Is there any way not to update some row cells if the parameter is not defined without looping through every of them and unsetting them?</p>  <pre><code>unset($this-&gt;created_at); </code></pre>  <p>Thanks, Marius</p>